PlantCoin Bot

PlantCoin is a Telegram reward bot written in Rust that aims to create a sustainable micro-reward ecosystem where users can earn small payouts through tasks and interactions.

The project is built using async Rust, focusing on performance, reliability, and long-term scalability.

⚠️ The project is currently in early development and features may change as the platform evolves.

Features

Current implemented features:

Telegram bot built with Teloxide
SQLite database for user storage
Automatic user registration
Balance tracking system
Basic reward harvesting system
Inline keyboard interaction
Command handling system

Example commands:

/start
/username
/saldo
/colher

Inline buttons allow users to:

check their username
view balance
claim rewards
Project Goals

The long-term vision of PlantCoin is to evolve into a Telegram-based reward platform combining elements such as:

Faucet mechanics
Micro-tasks
Ad-based rewards
Investment or staking systems
Automated payouts

The goal is to build a sustainable reward ecosystem that can operate long-term.

Tech Stack

PlantCoin is built with modern Rust async technologies.

Core stack:

Rust (Edition 2024)
Tokio (async runtime)
Teloxide (Telegram bot framework)
SQLite (database)
Rusqlite (SQLite bindings)
Dotenvy (environment variables)
Pretty Env Logger (logging)
Architecture

The project currently uses a simple modular structure:

src/
 ├── main.rs
 ├── banco.rs
 └── telegram.rs
main.rs

Handles:

bot initialization
dispatcher setup
database initialization
banco.rs

Responsible for:

SQLite connection
user storage
balance management
telegram.rs

Handles:

command processing
callback queries
Telegram interactions
Installation

Clone the repository:

git clone https://github.com/thesomeypo/TGPlantCoin_bot.git
cd plantcoin_bot

Create a .env file:

TELOXIDE_TOKEN=your_telegram_bot_token

Run the bot:

cargo run

The SQLite database will be created automatically.

Database

Current database schema:

usuarios
---------
id
telegram_id
saldo
colheita_cooldown

Each user is automatically inserted on first interaction.

